Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Software Development Engineer II* role with *NextEra Analytics*. I bring over three years of professional experience building backend systems and production AI agents, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

Across Sperse and Qualitest, I have repeatedly taken ambiguous requirements and turned them into *customer-centric solutions*. At Sperse, I architected in ambiguity, translating loosely defined stakeholder workflows into *technical requirements* and *technical design documentation* for a *multi-agent* CRM platform in *Python*, *LangGraph*, *LangChain*, and *FastAPI*. I also built a *React* Flow and *TypeScript* workflow builder to *rapidly prototype* *full-stack* agentic swarms with product stakeholders, and shipped an *AI-assisted development* code review pipeline with *OpenAI Codex* and a custom Bitbucket MCP server that created *feedback loops for coding agents*, *system testing*, *unit tests*, and security guardrails across 25–30 PRs per week. That combination of rapid prototyping, secure design, and *CI/CD* discipline matches the technical depth this role demands.

At Qualitest, I worked on production services that required careful operational thinking and strong business communication. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis*, supporting uploads, downloads, and deletions across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO*. I also tuned *PostgreSQL*, surfaced the data in *React* dashboards, and partnered with business stakeholders to refine *product requirements* and *high level software design* decisions. On the operations side, I orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions*, reducing *AWS Lambda* timeouts and improving error recovery across *100K+* weekly executions. Together, these projects map closely to your focus on production standards, *observability*, *alerting*, *runbooks*, and *recovery paths*.

NextEra Energy's mission to help create a more sustainable world, together with its focus on *excellence* and *doing the right thing*, aligns with how I approach engineering. I would value the opportunity to contribute to a team that turns business objectives into dependable software and collaborates closely with product, security, and platform partners to support that mission. Thank you for your time and consideration; I would welcome the chance to discuss how my experience can support NextEra Analytics' work in planning, siting, forecasting, and optimizing energy projects.

